wlanpi-hwtest (1.0.12) unstable; urgency=medium

  * rpi-eeprom-config: check for presence of POWER_OFF_ON_HALT=1
  * rpi-eeprom-update: check for 0 return code
  * depends: add raspi-gpio
  * fan_test: turn fan on for 5 seconds and then turn off
  * oled: fix bug preventing OLED from starting
  * oss: update SPDX identifiers from BSD-3 to BSD-3-Clause
  * default behavior change: oled is now not engaged by default
  * default behavior change: autostart is now not started by default
  * bluetooth_test: ignore up/down status

